                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/ital-310" class="program-course-title">
              ITAL 310 The Invention of Italian Literature (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-28620" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Languages, Literatures and Cultures (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Italian (Arts)              : The course presents Italian's major texts and authors over the ages, by critically exploring how the invention of Italian literature impacts the formation of a national identity.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Matteo Soranzo (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Fall</li>
              <li>Given in Italian</li>
              <li>Prerequisite(s): ITAL250 or above, from amongst courses taught in Italian or permission of Department.</li>
              <li>Restriction(s): Not open to students who have taken ITAL 280.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

